# Description
A list of suspicious sybil addresses: These addresses have been identified based on an analysis of transaction data and conditions explained in the methodology and analyzed on my dashboard.
The first 174 wallets are main_wallets (defined on methodology), each having between 20 and 8,804 related wallets based on my analysis. The other 27481 wallets are related_wallets (defined on methodology), which are part of clusters. In this analysis I defined clusters as having more than 10 transactions between each other.
All documents detailing the relationships, including transaction hash, block timestamps, etc for each wallet, can be found on my dashboard. While some wallets may not have any relations on the LayerZero realted platforms, they may have numerous relations on other platforms/blockchains or at different times. These relationships are also available on my dashboard. You only need to search for each wallet address you wish to investigate on the dashboard.
My dashboard: https://flipsidecrypto.xyz/Mrfti/2024-05-18-08-54-pm-4hcPY6

# Detailed Methodology & Walkthrough
In this analysis, I used the flipsidecrypto external.layerzero.fact_transactions_snapshot table to find information related to LayerZero users before the snapshot. I tried to find related addresses by analyzing all of their activity on EVM chains, including Ethereum, Arbitrum, Optimism, Polygon, Avalanche, BSC, Gnosis, Base, Blast, and Aurora.
In this analysis:
The minimum related wallets are defined as 20 wallets, meaning a wallet should be related to at least 20 wallets to be included in the list. This criterion is selected by the LayerZero team and can't be changed.
Being related is defined as having at least 10 transactions between two wallets. If two wallets have more than 10 two-way transactions, then they are defined as related wallets (sybil suspicious). This criterion is selected by me and can change to any other numbers.
Terminology:
 main_wallets: Primary wallets under investigation or analysis.
 related_wallet: Wallets associated with a main wallet through transactions/interactions.
 total_related_wallets: Total number of wallets connected to a main wallet.
 related_transactions_count: Number of transactions between a main_wallet and its related_wallet
